<section id="command-circle">
    <title>CIRCLE</title>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>CIRCLE</command> <parameter>radius</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
CIRCLE does not move the turtle.
It draws a circle based on the turtles position and the given radius.
The center-point of the circle will be the turtle's current position.
</para>

<para>
See also <link linkend="command-circle2">CIRCLE2</link>.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
    <programlisting><userinput>; a 2D example
CIRCLE 100</userinput>
</programlisting>

    <programlisting><userinput>; a 3D example
PERSPECTIVE
REPEAT 36 [CIRCLE 100 RIGHTROLL 5]</userinput>
</programlisting>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
